            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Hd1e108">Rubrica 10</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De seditionibus ciuium</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>
      ¶ De seditionibus ciuium. Rubrica. 10
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e115">ARistoteles polliti
      <lb ed="#V" n="12" break="no"/>corum libro
      <lb ed="#V" n="13" break="no"/>4. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e127">Ubi multum quid intermedium
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>minime fiunt conturbationes et dis
        <lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>sentiones polliciarum. Et magne ciuitates sunt
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>magis sine seditionibus propter eandem causam:
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>quia multum quod medium. In paruis autem
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>facile diuidere omnes in duo: vt nihil relin
        <lb ed="#V" n="19" break="no"/>quatur medium: et omnes fere egeni vel opulen
        <lb ed="#V" n="20" break="no"/>ti sunt.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e146"> /
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e143">Libro. 5. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e148">Ubique propter inequale
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>seditio est. Totaliter equale querentes: sedi
        <lb ed="#V" n="22" break="no"/>tiones faciunt. Minores existentes ciues:
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>vt equales sint: seditiones faciunt: et equales
        <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>existentes vt maiores. De quibus dissident
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>ciues sunt lucrum et honor.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e163"> /
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e162">c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e165">Debile quod
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>seditione diuisum est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e171"> /
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e172">7. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e173">Regnum ab extrin
        <lb ed="#V" n="27" break="no"/>secis minime corrumpitur: propter quod et mul
        <lb ed="#V" n="28" break="no"/>ti temporis est. Ex seipso plurime corrupti
        <lb ed="#V" n="29" break="no"/>ones accidunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e183">
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e188">Tullius de offi. li. i. c. 19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e187">Qui parti ciuium
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>consulunt partem negligunt rem pernitiosam:
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>in ciuitate adducunt: seditionem atque discordiam</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e195">
               <lb ed="#V" n="33"/> /
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e202">Idem philippicorum lib. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e199">Forenses cause
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>legens iudicia esse non possunt ciuili pace sub
        <lb ed="#V" n="35" break="no"/>lata.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e207"> /
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e214">Li. 2. et pe.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e209">Nec priuatos socos: nec
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>publicas leges: nec libertatis iura videtur ca
        <lb ed="#V" n="37" break="no"/>ra habere: que discordie: quem cedes ciuium: quem
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>bellum ciuile delectat: eumque ex numero ho
        <lb ed="#V" n="39" break="no"/>minum eiiciendum: et exterminis humane natu
        <lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>re exterminandum puto. Nihil hc ciue: nihil
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>hc homine deterius: non autem ciuis: aut homo
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>habendus est qui ciuile baellum concupiscit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e228">
               <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e232">¶ Mattheus in euange. c. 12. Omne regnum
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>in seipsum diuisum desolabitur. Et omnis ciui
        <lb ed="#V" n="45" break="no"/>tas vel domus contra se non stabit. <!--117.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e245">
               <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e256">Marcus in euangelio. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e249">Si regnum in se
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>diuidatur: non potest stare regnum illud. Et
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>si domus super semetipsa despiciatur: non po
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>terat domus illa stare.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e259">
               <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e272">Uegetius de re mili. li. 3. ti. 10.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e263">Nulla quam
        <lb ed="#V" n="51" break="no"/>uis minima natio potest ab aduersariis per
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>deleri nisi propriis facultatibus seipsam con
        <lb ed="#V" n="53" break="no"/>sumpserit. Nam ciuile odium ad inimicorum
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>perniciem preceps est: ad vtilitatem sue de
        <lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>fensionis incautum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e277">
               <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e292">Lucanus li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e281">Summum brute nephas ciui
        <lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>lia bella fatemur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e287">
               <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e304">Lex diges. ti. de captinis et postli. reuersis.
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>l siquis ingenuam. §. pe.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e291">Per ciuiles dissentio
        <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>nes: semper res publica leditur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e299">
               <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e319">Proclus de theologicis elementationibus
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>propo. 86.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e303">Partitio quidem dispergit et dis
        <lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>soluit vniuscuiusque potentiam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-d1e311">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Rd1e334">Prouerb. vulg.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34529-Qd1e315">Cita e perita quando la
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>e diuisa.
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>Regno e conchiso da che le diuiso.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
